05/07/2005
EVROS, Greece -- Costas Karamanlis will be the first Greek prime minister to pay an official visit to Turkey in the last 46 years, international media reported Monday (4 July). 
The ANA news agency says he will travel to Ankara at the invitation of Turkish counterpart Recep Tayyip Erdogan. 
The dates will be announced later. 
Erdogan and Karamanlis discussed the planned visit during the opening of a gas pipeline project along the border at the weekend.
Also Monday, the Greek Finance Ministry announced plans for a scratch-off lottery game to raise money for the budget. 
The government hopes to earn more than 90m euros a year from the Xysto game. 
(ANA - 05/07/05; Japan Press, ANA, AP - 04/07/05)
